===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}}: a sharp peg — original form of {{och-l|杙|peg}}. Same as {{zh-l|*才}} and [[尗]].

===Etymology===
Traditionally connected to {{ncog|tbq-pro|*kyak|t=navel, umbilical cord, rope}}, the latter whence {{cog|my|ချက်|t=navel}}; however, the Old Chinese reconstructions make this problematic. Perhaps related to {{och-l|射|to shoot}} (STEDT).

